---
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <BaseHead title={"1. Neurobiological Foundations | " + SITE_TITLE} description="1. Neurobiological Foundations category page" />
    </head>
    <body>
        <Header />
        <main class="category-page" style="width: 75%; max-width: none; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px;">
        <header style="margin-bottom: 40px;">
            <h1>1. Neurobiological Foundations</h1>
        </header>

        <section class="category-article" style="margin-bottom: 40px; font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.8;">
            <p>Dreams are biological byproducts of the REM (Rapid Eye Movement) cycle. Neuroscientifically, the brain’s amygdala fires intensely while the prefrontal cortex—the seat of logic—remains dormant. This imbalance explains why dreams are emotionally vivid yet logically bizarre. This stage is crucial for neuroplasticity and memory consolidation, acting as a "nightly cleanup" to process information. Understanding this biological engine moves interpretation from mysticism to evidence-based mental wellness.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="category-wp-content">
<figure class="wp-block-uagb-image__figure"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="/media-images/posts/rem-sleep-neuroscience-illustration-1.jpeg" alt="Illustration for 1. Neurobiological Foundations" class="uag-image-14" width="1200" height="550" title="1. Neurobiological Foundations" role="img"></figure>
</section>



<section class="category-keywords" style="margin: 40px 0; padding: 20px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);">
    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 20px; font-size: 1.3rem;">Related Keywords</h3>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 10px;">
        <a href="/blog/brain-waves-during-rem-sleep/" class="keyword-btn active" style="padding: 8px 16px; background-color: var(--accent, #A78BFA); color: #1A0E33; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.95rem; transition: opacity 0.2s;">#brain waves during rem sleep</a>
        <a href="/blog/why-do-dreams-feel-real-science/" class="keyword-btn active" style="padding: 8px 16px; background-color: var(--accent, #A78BFA); color: #1A0E33; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.95rem; transition: opacity 0.2s;">#why do dreams feel real science</a>
        <a href="/blog/rem-sleep-and-memory-consolidation-study/" class="keyword-btn active" style="padding: 8px 16px; background-color: var(--accent, #A78BFA); color: #1A0E33; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.95rem; transition: opacity 0.2s;">#rem sleep and memory consolidation study</a>
        <a href="/blog/dreams-brain-emotion-sleep/" class="keyword-btn active" style="padding: 8px 16px; background-color: var(--accent, #A78BFA); color: #1A0E33; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.95rem; transition: opacity 0.2s;">#neurobiology of dreaming and emotional processing</a>
        <a href="/blog/role-of-amygdala-in-dreams-guide/" class="keyword-btn active" style="padding: 8px 16px; background-color: var(--accent, #A78BFA); color: #1A0E33; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.95rem; transition: opacity 0.2s;">#role of amygdala in dreams</a>
    </div>
</section>




        


<div class="category-faq-section" style="margin-top: 60px; padding: 40px 30px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04); backdrop-filter: blur(12px); -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px); border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);">
    <h2 style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 40px; color: #E2DCF5; font-size: 2rem; font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; text-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.35);">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="faq-content" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 24px;">

        <div class="faq-item" style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04); backdrop-filter: blur(12px); -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); border-radius: 16px; padding: 24px; border-left: 4px solid var(--accent, #A78BFA); box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.3); transition: transform 0.2s ease;">
            <h4 style="color: var(--accent, #A78BFA); margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 600;">Q: Why forget dreams?</h4>
            <p style="color: #E2DCF5; margin: 0; line-height: 1.7; font-size: 1.05rem;"><strong>A:</strong> Low norepinephrine</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item" style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04); backdrop-filter: blur(12px); -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); border-radius: 16px; padding: 24px; border-left: 4px solid var(--accent, #A78BFA); box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.3); transition: transform 0.2s ease;">
            <h4 style="color: var(--accent, #A78BFA); margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 600;">Q: Do animals dream?</h4>
            <p style="color: #E2DCF5; margin: 0; line-height: 1.7; font-size: 1.05rem;"><strong>A:</strong> Yes, mammals do</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item" style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04); backdrop-filter: blur(12px); -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); border-radius: 16px; padding: 24px; border-left: 4px solid var(--accent, #A78BFA); box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.3); transition: transform 0.2s ease;">
            <h4 style="color: var(--accent, #A78BFA); margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 600;">Q: Brain waves?</h4>
            <p style="color: #E2DCF5; margin: 0; line-height: 1.7; font-size: 1.05rem;"><strong>A:</strong> High-frequency $β$ and $γ$</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item" style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04); backdrop-filter: blur(12px); -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); border-radius: 16px; padding: 24px; border-left: 4px solid var(--accent, #A78BFA); box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.3); transition: transform 0.2s ease;">
            <h4 style="color: var(--accent, #A78BFA); margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 600;">Q: Can we stop dreaming?</h4>
            <p style="color: #E2DCF5; margin: 0; line-height: 1.7; font-size: 1.05rem;"><strong>A:</strong> No, essential for life</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item" style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04); backdrop-filter: blur(12px); -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); border-radius: 16px; padding: 24px; border-left: 4px solid var(--accent, #A78BFA); box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.3); transition: transform 0.2s ease;">
            <h4 style="color: var(--accent, #A78BFA); margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 600;">Q: REM length?</h4>
            <p style="color: #E2DCF5; margin: 0; line-height: 1.7; font-size: 1.05rem;"><strong>A:</strong> Increases through night</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
    </main>
        <Footer />
    </body>
</html>
